## Common Mistakes

### Mistake: Hardcoding Blue

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
className="bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700"

// ✅ CORRECT
className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90"
```

### Mistake: Using focus Instead of focus-visible

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Shows on click
className="focus:ring-2"

// ✅ CORRECT - Only keyboard
className="focus-visible:ring-2"
```

### Mistake: Not Using cn()

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Classes conflict
className={`${buttonVariants({ variant })} ${className}`}

// ✅ CORRECT - Properly merged
className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant }), className)}
```

### Mistake: Arbitrary Values for Colors

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
className="bg-[#3b82f6]"

// ✅ CORRECT
className="bg-primary"
```

## Must Follow

1. ✅ Never hardcode colors - always use CSS variables
2. ✅ Always use `cn()` for className merging
3. ✅ Use `focus-visible` for keyboard-only focus
4. ✅ Use opacity modifiers for hover/active states (e.g., `/90`, `/80`)
5. ✅ Use `--radius` token for border radius
6. ✅ Follow class ordering conventions
7. ✅ Use semantic color names (primary, not blue)
8. ✅ Add `transition-colors` for smooth state changes
